</taxonomicName>
is currently known common in 
<collectingRegion id="1761C684F67DD920FB9EF97EFB22F90F" box="[1100,1199,1704,1730]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="9" pageNumber="159">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
, northern and western 
<collectingRegion id="1761C684F67DD920FF5AF91AFF66F92B" box="[136,235,1740,1766]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="9" pageNumber="159">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
, and eastern 
<collectingRegion id="1761C684F67DD920FEAAF91BFE5CF92A" box="[376,465,1741,1767]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="9" pageNumber="159">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="ADB248F6F67DD920FE09F91AFD93F92B" box="[475,542,1740,1766]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="159">China</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="4D9E14E3F67DD920FDFEF91AFDE2F92A" box="[556,623,1740,1767]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="9.[136,229,1132,1154]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,351,1108]" captionTargetId="figure-101@9.[170,1417,351,1108]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 9. Distribution map of Synotis guizhouensis (☆), S. damiaoshanica (★), S. austroyunnanensis (▲) and S. sinica (●)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450795" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450795/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="159">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). It grows at the forest margin or under mixed forests with little understory at 
<quantity id="125DA583F67DD920FF71F926FEB3F8C6" box="[163,318,1776,1803]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="9" pageNumber="159" unit="m" value="1900.0" valueMax="2200.0" valueMin="1600.0">1600–2200 m</quantity>
elevations.
</paragraph>
